    "question": "A orchard field in Pampanga with clay loam soil has SCS curve number CN = 65 (AMC-III). Rainfall depth is 200 mm from a 24-hour storm. Antecedent moisture condition is III. The field is reduced till. What is the direct runoff in mm?",
    "options": [
      "172.65",
      "96.34",
      "172.65",
      "103.66"
    ],
    "correctAnswer": 1,
    "solution": {
      "keyConcept": "SCS-CN method: Q = (P - Ia)² / (P - Ia + S) where S = 25400/CN - 254 and Ia = 0.2S. Runoff only occurs when P > Ia.",
      "steps": [
        "S = 25400 / 65 - 254 = 136.77 mm",
        "Ia = 0.2 × 136.77 = 27.35 mm",
        "Q = (200 - 27.35)² / (200 - 27.35 + 136.77) = 96.34 mm"
      ],
      "formula": "Q = (P - Ia)² / (P - Ia + S)",
      "derive": "SCS method: S = 25400/CN - 254 (mm). Ia = 0.2S (initial abstraction). Runoff Q = (P - Ia)² / (P - Ia + S) when P > Ia. If P ≤ Ia then Q = 0. Derived from: Q/P = (P - Ia) / (P - Ia + S) — ratio of runoff to rainfall."
    }
